1 in writing to the applicant why the department is not able to complete development of a TMDL in accordance
2 with subsection (9)(a)(ii). The department and the applicant shall make reasonable efforts to mutually agree in
3 writing to a timeframe in which the department shall complete development of the TMDL. If the department
4 specifies a lack of resources as a reason why the department cannot complete development of the TMDL in
5 accordance with subsection (9)(a)(ii), the department shall clearly explain in its written specification what
6 resources are not available, why those resources are not available, and when those resources will be available.
7 (c) If the department and the applicant cannot mutually agree to a timeframe in accordance with
8 subsection (9)(b), the department shall, within 60 days of the department's receipt of the application, specify in
9 writing to the applicant the timeframe in which the TMDL will be completed by the department and the reasons
10 why that timeframe is appropriate. If the department specifies a lack of resources as a reason why the
11 department's timeframe is appropriate, the department may request the applicant provide funding for the
12 development of the TMDL in order to accelerate the completion of the TMDL.
13 (d) The applicant may, within 15 days of the department's written specification provided in
14 accordance with subsection (9)(c), request in writing a hearing before the board for the purpose of petitioning
15 the board to reverse or modify the department's decision. The contested case provisions of the Montana
16 Administrative Procedure Act, Title 2, chapter 4, part 6, apply to a hearing before the board under this
17 subsection. If the parties to the contested case waive a formal proceeding pursuant to 2-4-603, the informal
18 proceeding must be conducted within 30 days after the board's receipt of the written request. After the hearing
19 and in a reasonable time, the board shall affirm, modify, or reverse the action of the department, and the board
20 shall make findings and conclusions that explain its decision. Pending the board's decision, the department
21 shall develop the TMDL in accordance with the timeframe specified in subsection (9)(a)(ii).
22 (e) The department may not declare an application incomplete or deficient because a TMDL has
23 not been prepared.
24 (f) If on April 27, 2015, an application for a new individual permit to discharge into a surface water
25 body or a segment of a surface water body pursuant to 75-5-401 is pending, the surface water body or segment
26 of a surface water body has been listed pursuant to subsection (2) of this section, the discharge would contain
27 a pollutant for which the water body or segment is threatened or impaired, and a TMDL has not been developed
28 for the water body or segment, the department shall, except as provided in subsection (9)(g), complete a TMDL
